    "en": {
      "title": "Government notification regarding rice",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Agriculture Minister Mahinda Amaraweera said that till the end of this year there will be no shortage of rice in the country due to more than 5 lakh hectares of agricultural activities.",
        "He said the above while addressing a press conference held today (24) at the Government Information Department.",
        "Continuing his speech, he said that the current government's aim is to expand rice cultivation and stop the import of rice in the next year, and it is worrying that Sri Lanka is ranked 5th in the list of food and inflation."
      ],
